name: Two-Containers-MVC
description: In Spring Web Applications, there are two types of container, each of which is configured and initialized differently. One is the “Application Context” and the other is the “Web Application Context”. Lets first talk about the “Application Context”. Application Context is the container initialized by a ContextLoaderListener or ContextLoaderServlet defined in the web.xml.  The other context is the “WebApplicationContext” which is the child context of the application context. Each DispatcherServlet defined in a Spring web application will have an associated WebApplicationContext.
